<p class="">    <h1>Key Challenges and Potential Growth Opportunities in the Cannabis Infused Drinks Market</h1>    <h2>Challenges</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Regulatory Hurdles:</strong> The cannabis market is heavily regulated, with varying laws across different jurisdictions. This creates complexities for manufacturers in terms of compliance with local, state, and federal regulations.</li>        <li><strong>Consumer Perception:</strong> Public perception of cannabis-infused products is still evolving. Stigma and misinformation can deter potential consumers, limiting market growth.</li>        <li><strong>Ingredient Sourcing and Quality Control:</strong> Sourcing high-quality cannabis and other natural ingredients presents challenges related to consistency and safety, which are critical for maintaining brand integrity.</li>        <li><strong>Market Competition:</strong> As the cannabis beverage sector gains traction, competition is intensifying. New entrants and established beverage companies are vying for market share, making differentiation crucial.</li>        <li><strong>Distribution Channels:</strong> Developing effective distribution channels remains a challenge. Many traditional retailers are hesitant to stock cannabis products, which limits access to consumers.</li>        <li><strong>Price Sensitivity:</strong> Cannabis-infused drinks tend to be more expensive than traditional beverages. Price sensitivity among consumers can hinder sales growth, especially in price-driven markets.</li>    </ul>    <h2>Growth Opportunities</h2>    <ul>        <li><strong>Innovative Product Development:</strong> There is a growing demand for unique flavors and functional beverages. Innovating with different infusions, such as adaptogens, can attract health-conscious consumers.</li>        <li><strong>Health and Wellness Trends:</strong> The surge in health and wellness trends presents an opportunity to market cannabis-infused drinks as a natural solution for relaxatio